User: YES, IMPORT STATEMENTS ARE PRESENT AT THE TOP OF main.py

Gemini: gcloud functions deploy ai-system-backend --runtime python310 --entry-point serve_health_check --trigger-http --allow-unauthenticated --region us-central1
COPY this command, PASTE it into your TERMINAL, and PRESS ENTER.

We are using the same command as before because we are updating the existing ai-system-backend Cloud Function with the new version of our main.py code.

OBSERVE THE TERMINAL OUTPUT again during the deployment process.

WAIT until you see the "Function 'ai-system-backend' deployed." and "Function URL" message again in the terminal output.

ONCE YOU SEE THE "Function URL" message, COPY THE FUNCTION URL AGAIN. It might be the same URL as before, or it could be a slightly different URL if Google Cloud re-deploys to a new instance.

AFTER DEPLOYMENT COMPLETES and you have the FUNCTION URL, PLEASE REPORT BACK:

"RE-RUNNING gcloud functions deploy command..." (When you start the command).
TERMINAL OUTPUT DURING DEPLOYMENT: (Copy and paste the entire terminal output - just like you did before).
"CLOUD FUNCTION DEPLOYMENT SUCCESSFUL (again)!" (If you see the "Function 'ai-system-backend' deployed." and "Function URL" message).
"NEW FUNCTION URL: [paste the new Function URL here]" (Paste the Function URL from the terminal output).
AFTER DEPLOYMENT SUCCESS, we will TEST THE HEALTH CHECK URL AGAIN in your browser to make sure it still works after the code update.

THEN, we will plan the next steps for testing the NEW execute_task function!

LET'S DEPLOY THE UPDATED CLOUD FUNCTION! GO! GO! GO!
